text: are you guys ready for your daily dose
of travel inspiration the following are
my 10 favorite travel quotes of all time
let's dig in if I'm an advocate for
anything it is to move as far as you can
as much as you can across the ocean or
simply across the river the extent to
which you can walk in someone else's
shoes or at least eat their food it's a
plus for everybody open your mind get up
off the couch move Anthony Bourdain a
man of ordinary talent will always be
ordinary whether he travels or not but a
man of superior talent will go to pieces
if he remains forever in the same place
Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart 20 years from
now you will be more disappointed by the
things you didn't do than by the ones
you did so throw off the bowlines sail
away from the safe harbor catch the
trade winds in your sails explore dream
discover Mark Twain travel makes one
modest you see what a tiny place you
occupy in the world Gustave Flaubert to
travel is to discover that everyone is
wrong about other countries Aldous
Huxley the more I traveled the more I
realized that fear makes strangers of
people who should be friends Shirley
MacLaine travelling it leaves you
speechless then turns you into a
storyteller even basura a mind that is
stretched by a new experience can never
go back to its old dimensions
Oliver Wendell Holmes stuff your eyes
with wonder live as if you drop dead in
ten seconds see the world it's more
fantastic than any dream made or paid
for in factories Ray Bradbury life is
either a daring adventure or nothing at
all
Helen Keller I hope these 10 quotes
inspire you to take your next trip and
book your next plane ticket because
there's an entire world out there
waiting for you to visit I'm driven ski
and if you like my travel videos please
click Subscribe and join me as I plan to
visit every country in the world
